I"É<p>Rather than having <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/meshing-discretizes-continuous-spaces">discrete</a> separate <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memory-is-perception-of-structural-artifacts">systems</a> supporting <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-buffer-is-like-short-term-memory">short-term</a>, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-contents-resemble-long-term-memory">long-term</a>, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/working-memory-recruits-sensory-areas-for-housing-representations">working memory</a> etc., the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brain-is-like-hardware-mind-is-like-software">brain</a> uses a cascade of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memory-is-like-a-manuscript">memory systems</a> at all time scales, from the millisecond-scale memory of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/experiential-scarcity-fosters-appreciation">Now</a>, to the decade-scale <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/invariant-of-consciousness-supports-fuzzy-duplicates">psychological</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/how-can-routine-cell-replacement-permit-psychological-continuity">continuity</a>.</p>
